VIBE CODING — COMMERCIAL EXCEPTION ADDENDUM

Applies to: Vibe Coding License v0.9-proof-stable

⸻

1. Purpose

This Commercial Exception Addendum defines the only circumstances under which commercial use of the Vibe Coding Software, methodology, or associated materials is permitted.

Absent an approved exception, all commercial use is prohibited.

⸻

2. Definition of Commercial Use

For purposes of this Addendum, Commercial Use includes, but is not limited to:
	•	Selling access to the Software or derivatives
	•	Offering paid consulting, coaching, or services primarily built on the Software
	•	Embedding the Software into a paid product or SaaS
	•	White-labeling or rebranding the Software
	•	Monetizing workflows, templates, or outputs generated directly from the Software
	•	Using the Software as a customer-facing core system in a for-profit offering

⸻

3. Eligible Commercial Exceptions

Commercial use may be granted under one of the following models only with written approval:

3.1 Client-Specific Internal Deployments

Permitted when:
	•	The Software is used internally for a single organization or client
	•	The Software is not resold, sublicensed, or redistributed
	•	Branding and logos are removed or replaced
	•	The client understands the Software is not a Vibe Coding product

Typical use cases:
	•	Internal dashboards
	•	Process prototyping
	•	One-off internal automation proofs

⸻

3.2 Educational & Training Programs

Permitted when:
	•	Used as part of a curriculum or workshop
	•	Participants do not receive redistribution rights
	•	Branding is preserved or replaced per written terms
	•	The Software is not marketed as the instructor’s proprietary system

⸻

3.3 Revenue-Share or Partnership Agreements

Permitted when:
	•	A formal partnership agreement exists
	•	Revenue share or licensing terms are defined
	•	Branding usage is explicitly approved
	•	IP ownership boundaries are documented

⸻

4. Non-Transferability

Commercial exceptions:
	•	Are non-transferable
	•	Are limited in scope and duration
	•	Do not create precedent for future permissions
	•	May be revoked if terms are violated

⸻

5. Attribution Requirements (When Approved)

When a commercial exception is granted, attribution must follow one of the following (as specified in writing):
	•	“Built using Vibe Coding methodology (licensed use)”
	•	“Inspired by Vibe Coding (with permission)”

No use of logos or branding is permitted unless explicitly authorized.

⸻

6. Prohibited Representations

Even with a granted exception, you may not:
	•	Claim ownership of the Vibe Coding methodology
	•	Represent the Software as an official Vibe Coding product
	•	Imply endorsement without written approval
	•	Use Vibe Coding branding outside the approved scope

⸻

7. Termination

Violation of this Addendum immediately terminates the commercial exception and reverts usage to the base license restrictions.

⸻

8. Contact for Exceptions

All commercial exception requests must be submitted in writing to the copyright holder.

Approval is discretionary and may be denied without explanation.
